                      Silver celebration on stage                    Rounding off its phenomenal popularity among Bengals theatre-loving audience, Nandikar hosts its 25th annual National Theatre Festival featuring leading troupes from all over the country as well as from beyond its borders. A prestigious event on the cultural calendar, this years festival is dedicated to the memory of Indian playwrights Vijay Tendulkar, Chetan Datar and Bangladeshi Selim Al Deen, who passed away earlier this year. Comprising 20 performances, 10 of which are for children and young people, it promises to do its bit in helping to transcend the general gloom and despondency in our hearts in the wake of the recent national tragedy. Besides staging of plays, an exhibition on childrens theatre and seminars on departed theatre greats are also on the cards. To be inaugurated this evening at 6, the festivals opening ceremony features a bouquet of songs Bhitara Bahire by local music band Mokam, presenting its unique range of a fusion of classical and folk tunes. This will be followed by a workshop production (dir: Per Sorberg) by trainees of a group from Sweden.                  Event: Nandikars 25th National Theatre Festival When: December 16 - 25 Where: Academy of Fine Arts and adjoining areas	                    
